reviews.review_text: Sound is pretty good I've only listened to the first set so far, but it's sounding very good.  The notes are for the previous night.  Do yourself a favor and listen to the entirety of the Dark Star>Playin' Reprise>Dark Star.  This may be the best of the modern day Dark Stars, a slight not over 7/12/90, although one could argue for the ones with Branford.  Don't skip the Truckin'>China>Rider either.  The first set's kind of blase after Feel Like a Stranger, but well-played.  Ramble on Rose picks up in intensity once Jerry gets the MIDI going.  One of my rare 5-star reviews for post-77 Dead.
